<TITLE> BDR seizes foreign pistol in Joypurhat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Joypurhat, May 03 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Rifles on Monday seized a foreign pistol, two magazines and seven rounds of ammunition from Panchbibi upazila in Joypurhat. Major Zakir Hossain an officer deputed to the BDR in the district said that they had acquired information of smugglers transporting Indian goods across the border of Chechra village under Panchbibi. Hossain also said that noticing the presence of BDR, the smugglers fled leaving the firearm and ammunition. bdnews
